        public net.proteusframework.internet.http.ResponseURL createConfigURL(CmsResponse response)
        Description copied from interface: ConnectorRegistration
        Create a config URL. This can be used with the data attribute, "data-ckeditor_config", on a textarea to be replaced by the CKEditor via FCKeditorHelper.fckactivate(textarea). You can also set this on an MIWT Field. 

           ResponseURL url = registration.createConfigURL(response);
   url.addParameter('some', 'extra_info');
   field.setRichEditorConfig(url.getURL(true));
